                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17528a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Special Representative <persName type="to">Rodgers</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-18T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 18, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Request General Carranza to issue necessary orders to appropriate Chihuahua
                    authorities to permit this Government to transport supplies for American troops
                    now in pursuit of Villa and his band over the Northwestern Railway from Juarez
                    to Casas Grandes or its vicinity. In making the request you will remind General
                    Carranza of this Government’s courtesy to him in repeatedly allowing his forces
                    to use the railroads of this country. Telegraph reply as quickly as
                    possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
